{"title": "Colonel's Dream", "description": "In this novel, Chesnutt described the hopelessness of Reconstruction in a post-Civil War South that was bent on reestablishing the former status quo and rebuilding itself as a region of the United States where new forms of \"slavery\" would replace the old. This novel illustrated how race hatred and the impotence of a reluctant Federal Government trumped the rule of law, ultimately setting the stage for the rise of institutions such as Jim Crow, lynching, chain gangs and work farms--all established with the intent of disenfranchising African Americans. - Summary by James K. White", "duration": 32736, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "2920", "name": "Charles Waddell Chesnutt"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/colonelsdream_1407_librivox/colonels_dream_1407.jpg", "copyright_year": "1905", "genres": ["Literary Fiction", "Published 1900 onward"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "James K. White"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "James K. White"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Bev J Stevens"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Laura Victoria"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Dedication & Chapter 1", "readers": [5985], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/colonelsdream_1407_librivox/colonelsdream_01_chesnutt_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1505}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter 2", "readers": [5985], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/colonelsdream_1407_librivox/colonelsdream_02_chesnutt_64kb.mp3", "duration": 601}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter 3", "readers": [5985], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/colonelsdream_1407_librivox/colonelsdream_03_chesnutt_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1217}, {"section": 4, "title": "Chapter 4", "readers": [5985], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/colonelsdream_1407_librivox/colonelsdream_04_chesnutt_64kb.mp3", "duration": 933}, {"section": 5, "title": "Chapter 5", "readers": [5985], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/colonel